2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on cellular networks and their optimization, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an iterative power adjustment algorithm to obtain the optimal power solution, which involves control theory concepts. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions the use of numerical results to illustrate the theoretical findings, which could involve multimedia applications. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper involves optimization of resources in cellular networks, which could be modeled using game theory concepts.
